The paper deals with the evaluation of web pages in the context of Information Retrieval, which is a subfield of Computer Science. The use of semantic evaluation and segmentation techniques suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The incorporation of multi-dimensional evaluation methodology and the use of annotations suggest that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Deep Learning (cs.DL), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
